content: Yes, I can provide you with some information. Central Station in Los Angeles is open 24 hours a day, 7 days a week, as it serves as the main public transportation hub for the city. This means that you can visit the station and see the "El Sol" mural by Yreina Cervantez at any time. However, keep in mind that certain areas of the station may be closed off during certain hours, so be sure to plan ahead and check for any closures or restrictions that may be in place.
